    "connections_to_other_philosophers": {
      "influence": "The *Tao Te Ching* has been linked to earlier Chinese traditions, including the *I Ching* (Book of Changes) and the concept of natural harmony found in Confucianism.",
      "contrast": "While Confucianism emphasizes social order and ethical conduct through structured rules and rituals, Taoism focuses on individual harmony with the Tao through naturalness and spontaneity. The *Tao Te Ching* also contrasts with Legalism, a Chinese philosophy that advocated for strict laws and punishments to maintain order."
    },
